"# Intestinal parasites\nAll siblings or children accompanying patients must be treated with a single dose of 500 mg of mebendazole. # Routine treatment during rehabilitation\nOne week after admission, when diarrhoea and vomiting should in principle have stopped and infection is either fully or partially under control, the following treatment must be given:\nVitamin A\nThe treatment provided under Section 4.6.1 above should be repeated for all TFC patients. # Intestinal parasites\nAll patients should be given a single dose of 500 mg of mebendazole. # Anaemia treatment\nAll severely malnourished children suffer from anaemia to some extent. After 15 days, when infection should in principle be controlled, all patients should therefore be given 1 mg of folic acid and 100 mg of ferrous sulphate daily for the duration of their stay in the TFC. # Routine treatment upon discharge\n\n# Immunization\nAll children should have been vaccinated against measles upon their admission, and be vaccinated again before their discharge."